Change Log for Releases
=======================

## [v0.1.0] - Initial Release

### Added
- HD44780-compatible 16×2 LCD driver  
- Support for 4-bit and 8-bit parallel data modes (D0–D7)  
- LCD core features:
  - Initialization sequence based on datasheet timing  
  - Command and data transmission  
  - Cursor positioning and display control  

- SHT11 temperature and humidity sensor driver  
- Custom 2-wire communication protocol implementation (non-I2C)  
- Support for transmission start sequence and byte-level communication  
- ACK/NACK handling for reliable data transfer  
- Measurement capabilities:
  - Temperature measurement  
  - Humidity measurement  
- Support for sensor resolution:
  - 14-bit (temperature)  
  - 12-bit (humidity)  

- Precise delay functions using SysTick:
  - Microsecond delay  
  - Millisecond delay  

---

### Platform
- Target MCU: STM32F103C8T6 (ARM Cortex-M3)  
- System clock: Internal High-Speed Oscillator (HSI)  
- Software architecture:
  - CMSIS-based implementation  
  - Direct register-level programming (no HAL)  

---

### Hardware
- GPIO Port A and Port B used for:
  - LCD interface  
  - SHT11 communication  

---

### Notes
- Initial functional release  
- Drivers are implemented using blocking operations  
- Focus on low-level control and hardware-oriented design  
- Designed for clarity, portability, and future extension  